 we should accept hypocrisy as a fact of politics--the most dangerous form of political hypocrisy is to claim to have a politics without hypocrisy. Featuring a new foreword that takes the story up to Donald Trump, this book examines why, instead of vainly searching for authentic politicians, we should try to distinguish between harmless and harmful hypocrisies and worry only about the most damaging varieties.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aHypocrisyxPolitical aspects. 0aPolitical ethics. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / State.2bisacsh  aAbsurdity.  aAffair.  aAnti-intellectualism.  aAutobiography.  aBehind a Mask.  aBernard Mandeville.  aBill Clinton.  aCambridge University Press.  aCareer.  aChristopher Hitchens.  aConscience.  aContingency (philosophy).  aCriticism.  aCynicism (philosophy).  aDe Cive.  aDemocracy.  aDespotism.  aEminent Victorians.  aEpithet.  aEthics.  aExistence.  aExplanation.  aFiction.  aGeorge Orwell.  aGood faith.  aHillary Clinton.  aHypocrisy.  aImperialism.  aInjunction.  aIntellectual.  aInternational relations.  aIrony.  aJeremy Bentham.  aLecture.  aLegal fiction.  aLegislation.  aLiberalism.  aLie.  aLiterature.  aLoyalty.  aMachiavellianism.  aMetaphor.  aMorality.  aNaivety.  aNeologism.  aNiccolò Machiavelli.  aNickname.  aObedience (human behavior).  aPamphlet.  aParty system.  aPatriotism.  aPhilosopher.  aPhilosophy.  aPhineas Redux.  aPiety.  aPious fraud.  aPoliteness.  aPolitical class.  aPolitical history.  aPolitical party.  aPolitical philosophy.  aPolitical science.  aPolitician.  aPolitics.  aPopular sovereignty.  aPragmatism.  aPrinceton University Press.  aPrinciple.  aPublic opinion.